<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Eddy</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-03"><hi rend="italic">October 3,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. Eddy to informally consult the Russian ambassador
                            and say that the United States Government would be pleased if he might
                            feel free to use at once his good offices and exert his influence, in
                            whatever direction, in aid of the rescue of Miss Stone, and states that
                            Mr. Eddy may, in the same way, invoke the aid of any other foreign
                            minister who may be able to render assistance.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>